      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED BULL BERNIE (8) was beaten only a nose into second at this circuit and distance after racing parked last week. Tackled the Gold Chalice series prior, placing in the heats and finishing only 4m away in a consolation. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but he looks close to a win. LUCKY PUNT (6) overcame a back row draw to win two back at this circuit and distance and was once again right in the mix last time out when runner-up after racing parked from a similar barrier to this, beaten 3.4 metres. Likely to be a major force again. MEMPHIS FURY (7) draws wide but is hard to knock off back-to-back wins, one here and the other from the second line at Parkes. BETTER BE SWIFT (5) ended a short maiden campaign with a win at this circuit and distance four months ago. Readied with two trials and has upside. Market watch.",
